{
  "components": [
    {
      "id": "in",
      "provider": "webhook",
      "config": {
        "mode": "Source",
        "parameters": {},
        "type": "webhook"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "agent",
      "provider": "agent_rocketride",
      "config": {
        "agent_description": "RIPPLE blast-radius copilot for Python repositories ingested into a Neo4j knowledge graph.",
        "instructions": [
          "Input is JSON with request_id, repo_id, mode, question, and intent. Preserve request_id exactly. First call ripple.memory_recall with repo_id and the question. Never invent graph facts or claim tests passed unless ripple.verify_patch says passed=true.",
          "Resolve a named symbol with ripple.resolve_symbol when needed. Call ripple.blast_radius for the chosen fqn; it returns ranked impact and exact read-only Cypher.",
          "Fix mode: call ripple.read_function_source and use memory.peek path source. Call ripple.prepare_sandbox once, poll ripple.job_status to done, and peek path result for sandbox_id. Inspect any test file before editing with ripple.sandbox_download.",
          "Draft a minimal complete git unified diff against exact source. Call ripple.verify_patch with the input request_id, repo_id, sandbox_id, diff_text, and changed production fqns. Poll to done and peek path result. On failure, use log_tail and retry a complete diff; maximum 3 verify calls.",
          "After passed verification, call ripple.open_draft_pr using that verify job id and its exact canonical diff. Poll a returned PR job; use null when PR is skipped. Call ripple.memory_remember with a concise note containing the decision, blast radius size, uncovered count, and failed verification attempts or fragility. Then call ripple.finalize_fix_result with input request_id, verify job id, PR job id or null, blast impact, blast Cypher, iteration count, and memory_notes containing the remember result.",
          "finalize_fix_result is the last fix tool. Next set done=true and answer exactly {{memory.ref:<finalize result key>:json}} with no wrapper.",
          "If the Wave budget is ending after exact source inspection and you have a complete diff but no verification result, set done=true and answer only JSON {\"mode\":\"fix\",\"repo_id\":<input repo_id>,\"request_id\":<input request_id>,\"changed_fqns\":[<target fqn>],\"diff_text\":<complete diff>}. Never put ellipses or assumed source in this handoff; the gateway will submit it to the same MCP and Daytona proof contract.",
          "Ask mode: use the earlier ripple.memory_recall result, resolve, call ripple.blast_radius, peek impacted[0:10] and cypher, then return only JSON {\"impact\":[...],\"summary\":str,\"cypher_used\":[...],\"memory_notes\":[...]}. Quote relevant recalled notes verbatim and label them from repo memory. Use at most 10 impacts."
        ],
        "max_waves": 12,
        "parameters": {}
      },
      "input": [
        {
          "lane": "questions",
          "from": "in"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "agent_llm",
      "provider": "llm_openai_api",
      "config": {
        "profile": "custom",
        "custom": {
          "model": "openai/gpt-4.1-nano",
          "base_url": "https://models.github.ai/inference",
          "modelTotalTokens": 1048576,
          "apikey": "${ROCKETRIDE_GITHUB_TOKEN}"
        },
        "parameters": {}
      },
      "control": [
        {
          "classType": "llm",
          "from": "agent"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "mem",
      "provider": "memory_internal",
      "config": {
        "type": "memory_internal"
      },
      "control": [
        {
          "classType": "memory",
          "from": "agent"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "ripple_tools",
      "provider": "mcp_client",
      "config": {
        "serverName": "ripple",
        "transport": "streamable-http",
        "endpoint": "${RIPPLE_MCP_ENDPOINT}",
        "headers": {},
        "bearer": ""
      },
      "control": [
        {
          "classType": "tool",
          "from": "agent"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "out",
      "provider": "response_answers",
      "config": {
        "laneName": "answers"
      },
      "input": [
        {
          "lane": "answers",
          "from": "agent"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "project_id": "1535d2f1-611a-44f2-9f32-eaa0a21b9e88",
  "source": "in",
  "version": 1
}
